---
import { ACTION_ERROR_CODES } from 'astro:actions';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import GridArt from '../components/GridArt.astro';
import { paletteGridToBitmap } from '../lib/bitmap.js';
import bannerData from '../data/decor/reorganising-research-banner.json';

// Banner pixel art (180×47 index-grid → bitmap; same path as the essay covers).
const bannerArt = paletteGridToBitmap(bannerData, { size: 12, gap: 1, radius: 2 });

// Essay-prize submissions go to this inbox.
const PRIZE_EMAIL = 'essay@science.works';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Reorganising Research — Science Works"
  description="Reorganising Research, a workstream within the Institutional Dynamism project at Science Works. A call for evidence and an essay-writing prize.">
  <main class="rr">

    <!-- 1) Banner — title left, picture right  -->
    <header class="rr-banner">
      <div class="rr-banner-text">
        <h1 class="rr-title">Reorganising</h1>
        <h1 class="rr-title-2">Research</h1>
        <a class="rr-kicker" href="/projects#institutional-dynamism">Part of Institutional Dynamism &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div class="rr-banner-pic">
        <GridArt bitmap={bannerArt} fit="width" class="rr-banner-art" label="Reorganising Research artwork" />
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- 2) Intro blurb. -->
    <section class="rr-intro">
      <p class="bigger">Every era of scientific progress has rested on the invention of new ways to organise our efforts.</p>
      <p>The research university, the national laboratory, the corporate lab, the funding council, the mission agency – each was an institutional innovation with its own design choices, affordances, and limits, well-suited to some kinds of work and less to others.</p>
      <p>How labs and funding are organised, what incentives and timescales are hardwired into the system — these choices promote certain types of research and make others very difficult to pursue.</p>
      <p>The UK is unusually dependent on a single dominant model of research: the academic lab, funded by a patchwork of external grants, organised around a principal investigator, assessed primarily on papers, and built around a standardised career pathway. This model has supported much of what British science is rightly known for, and it will remain central.</p>
      <p class="p-short">But no single template serves every kind of research project. Recent initiatives and proposals – <a href="https://www.convergentresearch.org/about-fros" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Focused Research Organizations</a> (FROs), the <a href="https://aria.org.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Advanced Research and Invention Agency</a> (ARIA), <a href="https://institute.global/insights/tech-and-digitalisation/a-new-national-purpose-reimagining-uk-science-and-technology-through-lovelace-disruptive-invention-laboratories" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovelace Disruptive Invention Labs</a> – reflect the growing recognition that Britain would benefit from a broader institutional repertoire. Where variation is limited, there is less to learn from; the system struggles to evolve, and is less resilient.</p>
      <p class="p-short">The questions of whether our research base should diversify, and how, are only becoming more pressing: the existing system is under significant strain, while AI is transforming what research teams can achieve.</p>
      <p class="p-vshort"> <strong>Reorganising Research</strong> is a Science Works initiative to chart what mix of research institutions Britain now needs, and how to get there. We’re kicking things off with an <strong>essay prize</strong> and a <strong>call for evidence</strong>.</p>      
    </section>

    <!-- 3 + 4) Two boxes: Call for Evidence (left) + Essay Prize (right). -->
    <section class="rr-grid">
      
      <article class="rr-box">
        <h2 class="rr-box-title">Essay Prize</h2>
        <div class="rr-box-body">
          <p>We are launching an <strong>essay prize</strong> to uncover new thinking about how to reorganise research.</p>

          <p>We want provocations, reimaginings, and new data. We would much rather read a new argument that we disagree with than a familiar one we don’t.</p>

          <p></p>
          
          
          <p>Your entry can take any form you wish, <strong>but below are three prompts that we’d be interested in reading:</strong>
            <ol class="prompt-list">
              <li>Write a piece of speculative fiction exploring how the UK develops more diverse types of research institution diversification over the coming 5–10 years.</li>
              <li>Is the UK’s mix of research institutions right after all? How would we know if it weren’t?</li>
              <li>Identify a type of scientific or technological problem that cannot be adequately tackled inside existing research institutions. Explain why and identify a potential solution.</li>
            </ol>
          </p>

          <p>You don't need to be a researcher or to work in policy to enter — only to care about how organisational design shapes what science can do.</p>

          

          <div class="rr-details">
            <p><strong>Prize:</strong> £3,000</p>
            <p><strong>Runners up:</strong> £500</p>
            <p><strong>Length:</strong> Maximum 3,000 words (no minimum)</p>
            <p><strong>Closing date:</strong> 15th July 2026</p>
            <p class="rr-details-note">Winners and runners up will be informed by the 31st July 2026. Essays will be judged by the Science Works team. By submitting your essay, you agree that Science Works may publish it with full attribution. You retain copyright in your essay.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <a class="rr-btn" href={`mailto:${PRIZE_EMAIL}`}>To submit an essay, email {PRIZE_EMAIL}</a>
      </article>

      <article class="rr-box">
        <h2 class="rr-box-title">Call for Evidence</h2>
        <div class="rr-box-body">
          <p>Run jointly with the Wellcome Trust, this call for evidence will uncover examples of the labs, departments, institutes, programmes, and funding architectures across the UK that are doing things differently to the mainstream academic model.</p>
          <p>We are looking for organisations and initiatives that have stepped outside one or more of the mainstream assumptions about how research gets organised.</p>
          <p>This could include unusual team structures, financial models, governance arrangements, career trajectories, connections with other types of research organisation, or approaches to infrastructure.</p>
          <p><strong>We want to know how diverse our existing landscape really is, and what's already being trialled.</strong></p>
          <p>The most useful responses will come from people who can describe what their group or initiative is doing that wouldn't be obvious from its website.</p>
          <p>You can use the form to describe your own work, or to point us elsewhere. It takes around ten minutes to complete.</p>
          <!-- <p><a href="" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Find the form here.</a></p>  -->
          <p>This scoping exercise is part of a broader programme of work on institutional dynamism in UK R&D.</p>
          <p class="disclaimer"><em>With your permission, we may be in touch about future collaboration, use of your response to inform case studies, or events on this topic.</em></p>
        </div>
        <a class="rr-btn" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSflSbNqPm-C4Muu0ZN0Ujoe9sbpEMUX8JQKbxke0PTrzwBRTQ/viewform" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Fill out the form</a>
      </article>

    </section>

    <section class="email-footer">
        <p class="email-footer-text">For more information, please email <a href="mailto:laura@science.works">laura@science.works</a></p>

    </section>
  </main>

  <style>
    .rr { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 40px 40px 146px; }

    /* ── Banner ── */
    .rr-banner {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 40px;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 40px; 
      margin-bottom: 42px;
    }
    .rr-kicker {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
      font-size: 14px;
      letter-spacing: 0.03em;
      color: var(--text);
      text-decoration: none;
      opacity: 0.7;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      transition: opacity 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease;
    }
    .rr-kicker:hover { opacity: 1; color: var(--theme); }
    .rr-title {
      font-family: 'Antique Olive', sans-serif;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--theme);
      font-size: 52px;
      line-height: 1.04;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      margin: 0 -3px;
    } 

    .rr-title-2 {
      font-family: 'Antique Olive', sans-serif;
      font-weight: bold;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--theme);
      font-size: 75px;
      line-height: 1.04;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
      margin: 0 -6px;

    }
    /* Transform the wrapper, not the svg: the svg lives inside the GridArt
       component, so the page's scoped .rr-banner-art rule can't reach it. */
    .rr-banner-pic { display: block; transform: translateX(-55px) translateY(-12px) translateX(+15px) scale(1.35); }   /* raised 60px, 20% larger */

    /* ── Intro ── */
    /* full content width → right edge lines up with the banner picture */
    .rr-intro { margin: 0 0 56px; text-align: left; }
    .rr-intro p {
      font-family: 'Antique Olive', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 0 0 18px;
    }
    .rr-intro .p-short { margin-right: 50px; }
    .rr-intro .p-vshort { margin-right: 150px; }

    .rr-intro p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .rr-intro a { color: var(--theme); text-decoration: none; }
    .rr-intro a:hover { text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }

    /* ── Two-up boxes ── */
    .rr-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 14px;
      align-items: stretch;   /* equal height */
      /* pull the boxes out 31px (1px border + 30px padding) each side so the box
         text lines up with the intro's left & right edges */
      margin-left: -31px;
      margin-right: -31px;
    }
    .rr-box {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      background: var(--almost-white);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-grey);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 28px 30px;
    }
    
    .rr-box-title {
      font-family: 'Copperplate', serif;
      font-weight: normal;
      font-size: 24px;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 0 0 18px;
    }
    .rr-box-body { flex: 1 1 auto; }   /* grows so the button pins to the bottom */
    /* p.disclaimer beats `.rr-box-body > p` (specificity); tune this margin to taste. */
    .rr-box-body > p.disclaimer { margin-top: 28px; }
    .rr-box-body > p {
      font-family: 'Antique Olive', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 14.5px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 0 0 14px;
    }

    /* Custom counter so the number's position and its gap to the text are
       independently controllable (native ::marker can't be spaced reliably).
       Tune the ol `padding-left` for the number column, and the li `padding-left`
       for the gap between number and text. */
    .prompt-list {
      list-style: none;
      counter-reset: prompt;
      padding-left: 16px;        /* number column position (lower = numbers further left) */
      margin: 0 0 14px;
      font-family: 'Antique Olive', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 14.5px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--text);
    }
    .prompt-list li {
      counter-increment: prompt;
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 22px;        /* gap between number and text */
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .prompt-list li::before {
      content: counter(prompt) ".";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    /* Key facts block (essay prize) */
    /* padding-left 16px puts the block on the same columns as .prompt-list:
       square bullets line up with the list numbers, item text with the list text. */
    .rr-details { margin: 8px 0 0; padding-left: 16px; }
    .rr-details p { font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 4px; }
    .rr-details strong { font-weight: 700; }
    /* Key-fact items get a 10px --theme square bullet (the closing note doesn't). */
    .rr-details p:not(.rr-details-note) { position: relative; padding-left: 22px; }   /* text → 16 + 22 = 38px, matching the list text */
    .rr-details p:not(.rr-details-note)::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0.42em;
      width: 10px;
      height: 10px;
      background: var(--theme);
    }
    /* -16px cancels the block's padding-left so the note returns to the body-left edge. */
    .rr-details .rr-details-note { margin: 20px 0 0 -16px; opacity: 0.75; font-size: 13px; }

    /* Full-bleed red bar pinned to the bottom of the box. The negative margins
       (= the box's border + padding: 1+30 sides, 1+28 bottom) take it to the box
       edges; the matching 6px bottom radius nests into the card corners. */
    .rr-btn {
      display: block;
      margin: 24px -31px -29px;
      padding: 24px 30px;
      background: var(--theme);
      color: #fff;
      font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: 16px;
      text-transform: none;
      text-align: left;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
      transition: background-color 0.15s ease;
    }
    /* White arrow drawn from assets/brand via CSS mask: the mask uses the SVG's
       shape, painted with currentColor (white) — the source file stays red. */
    .rr-btn::after {
      content: '';
      display: inline-block;
      vertical-align: middle;
      width: 59px;
      height: 14px;
      margin-left: 10px;
      background-color: currentColor;
      -webkit-mask: url('/assets/brand/arrow-right-1_5x-solid.svg') center / contain no-repeat;
      mask: url('/assets/brand/arrow-right-1_5x-solid.svg') center / contain no-repeat;
    }
    .rr-btn:hover { background: #d4282a; }

    .email-footer { margin-top: 28px; font-family: 'Roboto', sans-serif; }
    .email-footer-text a { color: var(--theme); text-decoration: none;}
    .email-footer-text a:hover { text-decoration: underline; } 

    /* Smaller viewports - adjust params to avoid squash */

    @media (max-width: 940px) {
      .rr { padding: 40px 22px 72px; }
      .rr-intro { margin-bottom: 40px; }
      .rr-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 20px; margin: 0; }   /* no breakout once stacked */
      .rr-intro .p-short { margin-right: 0; }
      .rr-intro .p-vshort { margin-right: 0; }
      .rr { padding: 40px 22px 72px; }
      .rr-banner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-bottom: 40px; margin-top: 20px; }
      .rr-title { font-size: 36px; }
      .rr-title-2 { font-size: 62px; }
      .rr-intro { margin-bottom: 40px; }
      .rr-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 20px; }
      .rr-banner-pic { display: block; transform: translateX(-55px) translateY(-10px) translateX(+39px) scale(1.1); }   /* raised 60px, 20% larger */

    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
